<subSubSection id="C3695CD7FFE3FFA357DC4EF3FB9FC2A4" pageId="3" pageNumber="411" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="8BCC0F5CFFE3FFA357DC4EF3FC13C260" blockId="3.[151,1358,2806,3081]" pageId="3" pageNumber="411">
<emphasis id="B907D34EFFE3FFA357DC4EF3FE9AC248" bold="true" box="[152,307,2806,2835]" pageId="3" pageNumber="411">Taxonomy.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C7374DFFFE3FFA356074EF3FC81C248" authority="Desmarest, 1818" authorityName="Desmarest" authorityYear="1818" box="[323,808,2806,2835]" class="Mammalia" family="Noctilionidae" genus="Noctilio" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="411" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="albiventris">Noctilio albiventris Desmarest, 1818</taxonomicName>
, 
<materialsCitation id="3B1B0501FFE3FFA3547F4EF3FC1FC260" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3800754302" pageId="3" pageNumber="411">
“I’Amérique méridionale.” Restricted by A. Cabrera in 1958 to Rio Sao Francisco, 
<collectingRegion id="49B7C1BEFFE3FFA354464F27FCFAC260" box="[770,851,2850,2875]" country="Brazil" name="Bahia" pageId="3" pageNumber="411">Bahia</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F3644FCCFFE3FFA354204F27FC1FC260" box="[868,950,2850,2875]" name="Brazil" pageId="3" pageNumber="411">Brazil</collectingCountry>
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCC0F5CFFE3FFA357DD4F45FB9FC2A4" blockId="3.[151,1358,2806,3081]" pageId="3" pageNumber="411">
<taxonomicName id="4C7374DFFFE3FFA357DD4F45FE21C23A" authorityName="Desmarest" authorityYear="1818" box="[153,392,2880,2913]" class="Mammalia" family="Noctilionidae" genus="Noctilio" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="411" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="albiventris">Noctilio albiventris</taxonomicName>
is paraphyletic with respect to N. 
<taxonomicName id="4C7374DFFFE3FFA354374F45FC4CC23A" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" box="[883,997,2880,2913]" class="Mammalia" family="Noctilionidae" genus="Noctilio" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="411" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="leporinus">leporinus</taxonomicName>
. This has been proposed and confirmed using several different molecular markers, including mitochondrial and nuclear markers. Recent studies suggest that N. 
<taxonomicName id="4C7374DFFFE3FFA354C64F8AFBADC2EB" authorityName="Desmarest" authorityYear="1818" box="[898,1028,2959,2992]" class="Mammalia" family="Noctilionidae" genus="Noctilio" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="411" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="albiventris">albiventris</taxonomicName>
is a complex of at least three and maybe four cryptic species yet to be determined but roughly coinciding with the current subspecific arrangement. Four subspecies recognized.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
